Currency from Suryati's Peak for gear. Bring it to a Gelid Badge vendor.

This solvent is alleged to turn any mana-rich ingredient into liquid.

A special bomb designed to destroy archdevan magic constructs.
Mix Test, Unlimited use.
Map showing the direction of the mana wave via the mana measuring device.
[Throwable] Explosive used for training. Can be used at the Tower Base against scarecrows.
[Throwable] A special bomb designed to destroy dementaliths. Use near a dementalith.
[Throwable] Good for knots and restraints.
[Throwable] Monster spawns randomly by probability.
Token carried by Mystic of the Scions of Lok.
Token carried by Sorcerer of the Scions of Lok.
Token carried by Warrior of the Scions of Lok.
[Usable] An instrument that combines Mystic's Token, Sorcerer's Token, and Warrior's Token.
Mysterious fragment containing Lok's energy
[Throwable] A dart used by swineherds to control piglings.
[Throwable] An antidote to purify the evil plaguing the unicorn Seravy. Will only work if Seravy is weakened (below 30% HP).
Nearly incorporeal air energy used to activate the purifier. You can see a vortex in constant motion deep within.
[Usable] Inactive device for purifying blood magic. Will require a strong power source.
[Usable] Device for purifying the blood magic from the Thulsa's bloody tombstones. Must be in close proximity to use.
[Throwable] A sticky gel to cancel the curse on Kaidun's henchman, Ghufran.
[Throwable] Outer appearance means nothing. This brew will bear light on Kaidun's truth.
[Throwable] This droplet will entice the White Hart to follow you instead of attacking you.
[Usable] Use this to provoke and call Shakazen who is hiding at Shakazen's Refuge.
Secret Letter to Thulsan forces
[Throwable] Very large, very dangerous bomb. Use only as directed. Do not eat.
Rubbing of the Ancient Headstone
A book from Goddess Mystel that contains information about ancient myths.
Part of a document held by Lok's cultists. The writings are encrypted.
[Usable] A magical device that can be used to decrypt ancient codes.
Decrypted Scion document.
Barril de salgar.
Bland but readily available meat.
Sal grosso para conservar carne.
Carne conservada com sal dura muito mais tempo sem estragar.
Frogstongue Potion
Necroneutralizing Reagent to break Thulsa's imprisoning spell.
Liberation Stone
Often used as fencing.
Sharp metal scraps twisted into metal wire. Very useful for fences.
Wooden fence posts.
A report written by Whimnia.
Piece of leather with Lok's mark.
Used for making tracings of chiseled or textured stone.
A book that records the legend related to Shakan, the Beastlord.
Heroth's note to Siria.
A crate likely to contain plunder of the pirates. There also might be some secret information of the pirates.
Pendant worn by Adarak, who instigated chaos among the Giants. You must bring the pendant to Worlkir as proof of Adarak's death.
A sacred object made by combining various powerful magics. According to Mirak Bright, this sacred object can free the Giants.
[Usable item] A special bomb for destroying the dementaliths. Set this item near the dementalith to blow it up.
[Usable item] A dangerous bomb brought from Allemantheia to destroy the powerful dementaliths. Set this item near the dementalith to blow it up.
[Usable item] A scroll containing magic powerful enough to release the Wondrous Tomb Seal. If the magic of the scroll is used on the Sealing Stone...
It's a fragment gathered while inspecting the Resurrection Stone in the Temple of Dagon.
Mysterious potion made by Arcanist Klaon from herbs and Artful Gracebloom to clear to clear troubled minds.
This scroll is protected by magic.
Orders from Dakanius.
It bears the mark of Lok.
Records of the Scions of Lok.
A book written in some form of cipher.
Fragments of a destroyed dementalith.
The cold heart of the Countess. It's extremely cold. Seriously...don't lick it.
Red eye of the Count. It looks like it can still cast a spell on its beholder.
Draught made by Princess Arin using dewdrop buds and Rida's hair. Arin claims it's not dangerous...well, very dangerous.
Rida's letter for her little sister Arin.
Sedative made by Arin to get the Rebel Army under control. It looked as if she wanted the Rebel Army to die with this sedative.
A diary kept by a student of the Eldritch Academy.
These appears to be messages from the Scions of Lok.
Mattin's report from the Celestial Hills.
An old journal recorded by a miner.
An old hammer found inside of a crate. It doesn't look like it can be used as a weapon.
Old scissors found inside of a crate. They don't look like they can be used as a weapon.
A small bomb issued to blowup the weapon crates. It has a small destructive force, ideal for usage in caves.
A truth bomb that can identify the hidden Lok followers in Cutthroat Harbor.
A bomb issued to blowup the altar in the Dark Cathedral. It has enough powerful explosives to devastate the target.
This organic key seems to be an important part of Saleron's Sky Garden. Good thing you caught that caiman keybearer.
Samael's orders for Bruke.
Kinias's report on suspicious people in Cutthroat Harbor.
Korvin's report on suspicious people in Cutthroat Harbor.
Caton's report on suspicious people in Cutthroat Harbor.
Slawgesh's ledger.
Transaction ledger obtained from Slawgesh. It's encrypted so you can't read it.
A cipher carried by the Kazuur Syndicate. Perhaps it can decode their records.
A lance possessed by Kutmaschuk. Unlike the legendary weapon of a god that it is thought to be, it's fake and looks cheap.
Hair of the elin Princess Rida, who is in hiding at the moment.
An argon-created device found on the argonomorphed gula. What it does is unclear.
Portal token carried by Nurkrasid.
Portal token carried by Valursus.
Portal token carried by Masakrad.
Dazzling gem found on the dead bodies of Kaidun's soldiers.
A magic stone from the magical stone manufacturing device.
Magical ore mined in Fyrmount. It feels similar to lava. Prized in Castanica for its ability to generate power.
Belongings of miners.
Detrian's heirloom sword. You should return it to Hennika.
Small flute used to call upon the orcan cooperators. Only use at the secret meeting location.
Token left by General Kaidun, Fraya's lover.
An argon-created device found on the argonomorphed orcan. What it does is unclear.
Flame capturing Saleron's power. Only the power of a god can purify those who have been corrupted by the argons.
A note from Darekuur.
A key that can stop Killian's Necromancy Device.
Shana's report. Right-click to read.
Odorless white liquid used for very advanced alchemy. It can be used as a base to be mixed with Essence of Agony or Joy of Madness to create the Potion of Agony and Joy.
The agony of prisoners under torture captured in a bottle by magic.
The maniacal laughter of Killian's insane jesters captured in a red crystalline form. This strange gem makes the jesters laugh gleefully no matter what the situation is.
A potion that makes the victim feel both agony and joy. A terrible potion preferred by Killian's Torturers for inflicting emotional pain with their physical blows.
A mixture of agony, joy, and madness. This cacophony of emotions has an aura of evil energy. A fitting revenge to be used on the brutalest of torturers.
A key for accessing the true Throne of Nightmares.
A note from a Mysterium researcher.
An ancient treasure said to be able to reflect the determination of its beholder and transform it into power.
An ancient divine bottle that can hold Sikander's Holy Flame.
Detergent strengthened with magic for cleaning up various types of contamination.
It's very worn out with various forms of garbage on it. Can't really make out its original form.
A necklace worn by Mysterium members. There's a darkish-red blood stain on one corner.
A list of residents of Castanica snatched by the gulas. Might be worth reading.
A sedative that reduces the Vampirs' thirst for blood.
A device that detects lies.
Hard Naga skin stronger than steel. Can be sold at a good price to luxury buyers.
Chest full of gold looted by Naga Pirates.
Chest full of magical relics. Looks to be an offering to Dagon.
Blue jewel strongly infused with Dagon's power.
Key bestowed by Saleron to those who have passed the trial. Used to activate the Ancient Slate.
Key made from wyvern horn. Used to activate the Ancient Slate.
Key made from Dracoloth's scales. Used to activate the Ancient Slate.
Round ice stone resembling a pupil. Necessary ingredient to create the Vessel of the Gods.
Round fire stone resembling a pupil. Necessary ingredient to create the Vessel of the Gods.
Glacier fragment dug from the ice cap in the Vale of Spires. Necessary ingredient to create the Torch of the Gods.
Underworld energy compressed into a mass. Necessary ingredient to create the Vessel of the Gods.
Vessel for creating the Torch of the Gods. Created from the bonding of energy between the Ancient Slate and the Core.
Burn Kelsaik with holy fire! Use on Kelsaik to dispel the debuff immunity effect. You must use Torch of the Gods before debuff or stun Kelsaik.
Soul stone with traces of fear within.
A core containing the energy of an argon.
Potion created by refining traces of fear. Provides temporary immunity to Terror of Killian.
Totem powered by argon's core. Purifies poison in its surroundings. Can be used in Ebon Tower only.
Gem encrusted on Killian's staff. Can be used as a key for turning off the Sealing Device around the Ebony Tower.
Essence of the Core given by Fraya. Stop Kelsaik, Thulsa and Killian at any cost!
A fragment from the four original fragments of the Ancient Slate. You can feel the Holy energy within...
The report is intact, but heavily stained with blood.

Daily work report kept by the Instructor Witches. May shed a clue on why the witches have gone insane.
Investigation data of the ruins of Tyboth, the ancient giants' city.
Stone slab with unknown inscriptions and illustrations. It's stored in a large jar.
A box that contains magic extracting tools.
Cool refreshing water is in the barrel.
The Derasa Clam lives only in the deep sea. Its shells are washed ashore by the waves.
Bitterly sour fruit from the fragrant roses. While few will brave the taste, botanists claim it is full of vitamins.
Focus on the scent to refresh your mind.
A relic that seems to be abandoned by Lok.
The remains of Lok Followers.
Junk Eustace claims are important relics, but are not lost, even though he sent you to go find them.
Supplies that are to be sent to the Essenian Garrison who are fighting to seize a fortress.
Delicate flowers that grow in snowfields. Ingredient in a soothing tea.
Ore swirling with titanic energy.
A medicinal herb that has a mysterious smell.
Suspicious document of unknown origin.
A cold dark mass with a strange palpable energy.
An old relic inscribed with undecipherable characters.
Wood processed by lumbermen.
A flower that turns blood red when picked.
A twisty mushroom.
Stone with a slight hint of the temple's energy.
A dark blue berry with a nice tang.
Remains that look like bones from a villager.
Extremely hard, it is used for making cutting knives.
A debris that proves the tablet is destroyed.
Vines used for making traps.
It contains hunting weapons.
Fruit that Nagas enjoy. It is rare to find, making it hard to gather.
Found near Serpentis Isle, the stone contains five colors and is used for some unknown purpose. Prized by nagas.
Ore used by the ancient Giants.
Item left behind by the ancient Giants. Its usage is still unknown.
Tearroot grows in cold climates. It has a strong scent and has an anti-bacterial effect, making it useful for medicinal purposes.
These supplies should have been sent to the Advance Base, but they are just scattered around after an attack.
Flower that grows at the edge of cliffs. It is said to make wishes come true.
Flower grown from faerie magic, said to contain a bit of the fey spirit within.
Mushroom solid as rock. Must be roasted for days before softened enough to eat. It is therefore a rare delicacy and delicious.
It prevents faeries from losing consciousness.
Famous mushroom of Darkquaver Woods. It is traded at a high price.
Ore from the Croskurn Mines containing unique and powerful energy.
A rare plant grown only in the Valley of Death.
A mushroom that grew on the nutrients from the blood of the victims who fell from the bridge.
Stolen garrison food supply.
Marker necklace from a soldier tortured to death by Killian.
A red crystal emanating some bad energy. It resembles blood.
These spores are known to have a powerful sedative effect.
Fresh-laid basilisk egg is known as a delicacy.
An ice crystal that can be extracted from big bones.
Debris retrieved when destroying Mekonari's Bloodtomb Magic Stone.
A large fertile egg containing unhatched sikandari young. It feels warm.
Remains of an amani warrior who died in the Argon War.
A cold lump full of strong energy.
A small mineral shard that emits an endless, high-pitched but subdued sound.
A mysterious herb that emits a blueish phosphorescence. It has a bitter scent.
A device made of strange material. It looks like a natural ore lump rather than a component.
An ore with a natural flare pattern. Even separated from the ground, it still has some heat left.
A stone that emits a similar light to the light from a magical square.
Supplies of Devan brigands.
Journal of Sidurek. You cannot read because it is encrypted.
Fruit harvested from crops. It seems inedible.
All that remains of the kidnapped townsfolk.
A mysterious ore emanating a blueish phosphorescence.
A work of art found in the treasure box of the pirates.
Deserted timber from near the deserted house.
Supplies of the Kaidun army. It should help out the town.
A mysterious copy of the Core, source of the elves' power. It is yet unstable.
A bracelet marked with symbols of the evil god, Lok.
A tiny but beautiful blue flower.
A brief report from Basenius.
Creates a soothing agent. Found in the Azurice Shrine.
From yellow xanthic stones Found in the Azurice Shrine.
A potent energy source. Found in the Azurice Shrine.
For mining practice. Looks worthless.
Much stronger weapon than those used by the federation.
A potion with a crimson glow.
Yellowish-brown mushroom with coppery shine. It has a very sharp odor.
A blue Star Flower with a unique scent. It provides strong resistance against poison.
A crystal with a deep red hue as if it was solid blood.
A beautiful flower with mysterious energy. It's also used as an ingredient for medicine.
A fragment from an eldritch stone in the Celestial Hills. It hums audibly.
Its fragrance is sweet but there's hidden danger in its sweet scent. When the flower is fully bloomed, the aroma can induce headaches.
Medal awarded to the champions of the Valkyon Federation.
Bone pile that seems to be of an aman.
Protective stone created to protect the Goddess' garden. The stone is shattered.

Seaturn Set.
Sandturn Set.
Standard weapon for a secret group of elin mercenaries.
Standard armor for a secret group of elin mercenaries.
Standard gloves for a secret group of elin mercenaries.
Standard boots for a secret group of elin mercenaries.
From the refugess of the Lost Woods.
A thank you for your help at Camp Mournholme.
A momento of those who fled Pora Elinu.

A simple sign with a simple message.
Right-click to enter a message and place the sign at your current location.
Up to 10 characters can be entered. Text lasts for 6 hours.

Monkey with a message!
Right-click to enter a message and place the sign at your current location.
Up to 22 characters can be entered. Text lasts for 12 hours.

When only the teachings of a master will do.
Right-click to enter a message and place the sign at your current location.
Up to 22 characters can be entered. Text lasts for 24 hours.
A material for building a teleportal.
An ingredient for Hagand's invisibility potion. Reflective root confuses the casual observer.
The blood is used to show respect for the dead.
A truth serum to question archdevan prisoners.
Urgent letter from Dougal. Right-click to read.
An invisibility potion crafted for you by Hagand, chief archaeologist at Qeldar Station. Only usable in Diranas Quarry in Famine Valley.
A document recovered from an archdevan supply sack.
The remnants of a baraka's soul.
Urgent document from Gilbert. Right-click to read.
A needle filled with truth serum, useful for interrogations.
The fruit of the so-called moneytree. Named for its similarity to gold coins, which is why it is used as currency among goblins. It is otherwise worthless.
Decreases damage from projectiles for $time.
A box containing important mechanical parts of an airship.
A map to the archdevas' Energia Celo. The images on it seem to twist and writhe.
A lump of lime gathered from the Hina Hot Springs in Spring Valley. It's used to make a kind of magical glue.

Keezar made this glue by mixing lime with something that looked like mucus.
You have no idea what that sticky substance was, but why take chances?
A substance that the archdevan mystic Dyona asked you to deliver to Keezar. It has something to do with controlling demokrons.

According to Keezar, you can fix the broken archdevan pendant with this glue.
Whether it works or not, you're not touching it barehanded anyway.
The broken shards of the control pendant, glued together again with Keezar's Power Glue. Caution: Never try to wear it!
The shattered pieces of a broken archdevan control pendant—broken by the overconfident Cromagh.

Blatherweed, blooming in certain areas in Spring Valley.

"Some Anons believe that blatherweed can wake the dead, but that is not true. Yet, chewing blatherweed will clear your mind, and when made into tea, it revives your stamina. - Baraka Herbology"
Something you've found from a mysterious corpse. Right-click for a better look.
Hagand, the head of archaeology research lab, made this potion 10 years ago.
Portrait of Zolyn drawn by Paesyn.
Use it to make a stone grave for the fallen baraka.
An ingredient for invisibility potion. Foggy eyeballs impede the vision of others.
A key necessary to go into Energia Celo.
A stone used in the archdevas' experiments.
A potion that restores the senses of the addled, retrieved from a damaged medicine chest.
Teletransporta você para Highwatch.
Teletransporta você para sky cruiser dock em Velika.
Paesyn made this tonic in his neverending quest to make Zolyn like him.
The wise of Highwatch, Halran dropped this book. He sometimes forgets things, deeply emerged in meditation.
A moaloth's egg. Exceedingly rare.
